cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper deals with a cooperative communication scheme in a wireless body area network, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of time-division-multiple-access (TDMA) as an access scheme, which is a topic related to information theory. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The cooperative communication scheme used in the paper involves multiple agents (nodes) working together to improve performance, which is a topic related to multiagent systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper investigates the effectiveness of the cooperative communication scheme in mitigating interference in a scenario with multiple closely-located networks, which is a topic related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper employs on-body and off-body channel gain measurements to gauge performance, which is a topic related to multimedia.
